'''Magarpatta ''' ({{lang-mr|मगरपट्टा}} lit. ''Land of [[Magars]]'') is a 450 acre, privately owned [[gated community]] in the [[Hadapsar]] area of [[Pune]], [[India]]. It has a commercial area, residential area, hospital with several specialisations, shopping malls, restaurants, a gym, Aditi Garden (a 25-acre park) and schools. 30% of the area is made up of green space. There is a commercial complex named "Destination Centre" located herein.
==Management== Magarpatta was originally a farmland in Hadapsar, owned by the Magar family. They live in Hadapsar. Satish Magar is the [[chairman]] & [[managing director]] of the township.<ref>{{cite news|title=This developer let farmers retain their land|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/property-/-cstruction/this-developer-let-farmers-retain-their-land/articleshow/2417713.cms|date=1 October 2007}}</ref>
