==Awards== * Magarpatta won accolades at the Sydney World Congress of Metropolis in 2008. The Maharashtra Economic Development Council lists it among the ''Top 10 Success Stories of the State''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regus.co.in/coworking-space/india/pune/pune-magarpatta|title=Co-working In Pune, Magarpatta - Regus IN|website=www.regus.co.in}}</ref> * Magarpatta Township won the Best Residential Property in India at the CNBC Awaaz-Crisil-Credai Real Estate Awards, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/release/y2k10/jan/janrel59.php|title=RR Kabel presented the CNBC AWAAZ, CRISIL & CREDAI ‘Real Estate Awards 2009’|date=28 January 2010|publisher=}}</ref>
==In popular culture== ===Film===
* The climax scenes of the film [[Sivaji (film)|''Sivaji'']] (a 2007 Indian Tamil-language masala film) was shot at the Magarpatta city SEZ towers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wherewasitshot.com/sivaji-the-boss/|title=Sivaji – The Boss - Where Was It Shot|website=wherewasitshot.com}}</ref> * [[Mirchi (film)|''Mirchi'']] (a 2013 [[Telugu language|Telugu]] action drama) was also shot in Magarpatta city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wherewasitshot.com/mirchi/|title=Mirchi - Where Was It Shot|website=wherewasitshot.com}}</ref> * [[Andhadhun]] (a 2018 [[Hindi language|Hindi]] dark comedy thriller) was also shot in Magarpatta city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wherewasitshot.com/andhadhun/|title=Andhadhun - Where Was It Shot|website=wherewasitshot.com}}</ref>
